FBIS4-3564 "drchi078_f_94009" FBIS-CHI-94-078 Daily Report 21 Apr 1994 Near East & South Asia Delhi Radio Reports Border Talks With China Delhi Radio Reports Border Talks With China BK2104145494 Delhi All India Radio Network in English 1430 GMT 21 Apr 94 BK2104145494 Delhi All India Radio Network English BFN [Text] Border experts of India and China today began talks in Beijing on issues relating to the implementation of the agreement between the two countries on maintaining peace and tranquility along the Line of Actual Control in the border areas. The agreement was signed last September during the prime minister, Mr. Narasimha Rao's visit to China. The experts group set up during the visit is charged with several specific tasks, including reduction of troops, reconciling differences on the alignment of the Line of Actual Control, and avoiding actions that may give rise to misunderstandings.
